Step 1: Identify the necessary components.
• Total Current Assets at the beginning (2023-12-31): 8,000,000.00  
• Total Current Assets at the end (2024-01-28): 9,963,057.95  
• Main Business Revenue (from the income statement): 5,695,115.02  

Step 2: Calculate the Average Current Assets.
Average Current Assets = (Beginning Current Assets + Ending Current Assets) / 2  
= (8,000,000.00 + 9,963,057.95) / 2  
= 17,963,057.95 / 2  
= 8,981,528.975  

Step 3: Calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio.
Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Current Assets  
= 5,695,115.02 / 8,981,528.975  
≈ 0.634  

Rounded appropriately, this ratio is approximately 0.63.

Thus, the solution is:

{"solution": {"Current Assets Turnover Ratio": "0.63"}}
